latestPosts.caption:
Blondie’s Saturday Dump 🫶🏼
A little weekly roundup because so much happened—and it was all very Blondie.

☕ We went for a coffee tasting this week and tried some beautiful Ethiopian and Panamanian coffees. The caffeine high? Wild.
👀 Our copper bottles are finally here! They come in these super cute colors (pink!!), and we’re kind of obsessed.
📰 We woke up to see Blondie featured @bombaytimes. That was a fun surprise. 
👜 Our tote bags are clearly living their best lives- my brother took one to the farmer’s market in London and sent pics.
👕 A friend dropped by with a sample tee from her brand (and a uniform idea for us!)—our barista wore it and loved it.
💃🏼 Caught our head barista doing a little happy dance behind the counter. Good energy only.
🛍️ Our next drop? Some seriously cute new tote bag designs -launching June 28th. Can’t wait for you to see them.

That’s all for now. Back next Saturday. Same vibe, new stories. 💌

latestPosts.caption: Still thinking about how special the Nature Morte x Blondie day was. @adebayobolaji - layered with gold, wit, and a distinct echo of Jaipur transformed the space completely. Everyone was so focused at the Lino cutting table  broken only by bursts of laughter, the first sips of our cherry matcha (a sweet little debut), and a surprise round of tarot readings in the afternoon light. Thank you to everyone who came by, carved, lingered, and let the day unfold just right. More soon 🍒🖼️✨

latestPosts.caption:
Anadhya AKA our regular’s take on our monsoon menu ☔️

Bring your friends and come try her recc’s 🫡

(Blondie, bandra, monsoon menu, comfort, nostalgia, Khao suey, warm bowls)

Yesterday was so fun at the community table ☔️🫂 just good food, good people, and actual conversation. It felt easy and unpretentious, the kind of gathering where everyone’s genuinely enjoying themselves, not performing. Chef came out, I got to chat with everyone, and it turned into this really warm, open space where people shared feedback, stories, and just…hung out. These are the moments that make it all worth it, and honestly, we should do this more often. 

(Community table, blondie, monsoon menu, Bandra, mumbai)
